The 4th North-West Zonal Conference of the Social Studies and Civic Educators Association of Nigeria (SOSCEAN) will begin on Tuesday next week at the Federal College of Education Zaria, Kaduna state. According to a release by the Local Organising Committee (LOC) of the conference, a copy of which was sent to LEADERSHIP Weekend, the four-day event will be kick-started with an opening ceremony on Tuesday, February 4, 2020 at the El-Rufa’i Hall of the host college. The zonal conference, which has the theme: “Security Challenges, Peace-Building and Conflict Resolution in Nigeria: The Role of Social Studies and Civic Education,” will be chaired by the Dean of Arts, Social Sciences and Edudation, Ahmadu Bello University (ABU) Zaria, Prof. James Kantiok. Keynote address will be presented by a former member of the House of Representatives, Hon. Dr. Shehu Garba Matazu, while Dr. Abdulkarim Yunusa of Nasarawa State University, Keffi; and Dr. Yunusa Kadiri of FCE Kano, are both lead paper presenters at the conference. Also, the Kaduna state governor, Malam Nasir El-Rufa’i is the Special Guest of Honour; the Emir of Zazzau, HRH Alh. Dr. Shehu Idris CFR will be the Royal Father of the Day; HOD Social Studies, FCE Zaria, Dr (Mrs) P.N. Njoku is the Host while the Provost of the college, Dr. A.A. Ladan is the Chief Host, among other top academics and guests slated for the event. The conference, which will be attended by participants from Kaduna, Kano, Katsina, Kebbi, Jigawa and Zamfara states, will end on Friday, February 7, 2020 after days of plenary sessions.